commitResults.messageTitle: Update Duke class to greet, echo and exit
Update Duke to add and list text
Update Duke to be able to mark tasks as done
Add deadline, event and todo class and update Duke to support multiple task types
Add testing of Duke using I/O redirection technique
Remove displaying of the string "todo" unnecessarily
Update Duke to handle errors and update EXPECTED.TXT outputs
commitResults.messageBody: The task type ( todo, deadline and event) was previously included when a task description is printed. This is edited and Duke no longer prints out the task type in full.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Duke to handle more kinds of errors
commitResults.messageBody:
Throw DukeException when the following occur:
1. Description of any task type is empty, including case of when corresponding deadline/period is stated with no task description
2. When a word which Duke does not understand is inputted (does not start with todo, deadline, event and is not list or bye)
3. When user attempts to mark a task done when the number inputted is invalid (eg. 4 tasks but user inputs done 5)
4. Deadline/period for event is not indicated correctly. (/by and /at not used respectively, or when no deadline/period is stated for the corresponding task)

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Duke to be able to delete tasks
commitResults.messageBody: Duke can delete tasks and an exception will be thrown when the task number in input is not valid, or when the delete word is not followed by a task number.

commitResults.messageTitle: Edit code to be more succinct, edit behavior of Duke and update EXPECTED.TXT
